    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A gremlin? Oh, you noticed! They love to sneak into paperwork, you know. One of the bigger worries, besides the inspection stuff, is the *timing* and the *fees*. You need to know exactly how long that money is sitting there and what the escrow agent is charging for their services.\n\nThe escrow agent isn't just a glorified mailbox; they are the gatekeepers. They are supposed to be neutral, but sometimes, even the most honest-looking agent can be a little slippery, especially if they're trying to squeeze an extra fee out of you. Make sure you understand the disbursement schedule—when exactly will the money move? And check the fee structure upfront. Don't let any shady little contract clause make you sweat.",
      "source": "target",
